ices with varying network latencies\nfor Synchronous SGD. The novel thing about such a network is the ability of\neach machine to shut down and resume training capabilities at any point of time\nwithout restarting the overall training. To enable such an asynchronous\nbehaviour we propose a communication framework inspired by the Bittorrent\nprotocol and the Kademlia DHT.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 24 Nov 2018 19:11:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-27"}
